gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 114, Raptors 99
gameRecap.excerpt: The 76ers defeated the Raptors, 114-99. Joel Embiid led the way for the 76ers with 28 points, 13 rebounds and seven assists, while Tobias Harris (23 points, seven rebounds, three steals) and Kelly Oubre Jr. (23 points, five 3PM) added a combined 46 points in the victory. Scottie Barnes tallied 24 points, eight rebounds and eight assists for the Raptors in the losing effort. The 76ers improve to 3-1 on the season, while the Raptors fall to 2-4.
